@lukaskurz Thank you. I've found some notes in your PR, and it seems that your fix doesn't work anymore with version 3.3.
I guess this means i will step away from this plugin and Google Maps.
Edit: Successfully switched to flutter_map using MapBox.

This issue indeed seems to be fixed when adding the following code to `main.dart`:

```
import 'package:google_maps_flutter_android/google_maps_flutter_android.dart';
import 'package:google_maps_flutter_platform_interface/google_maps_flutter_platform_interface.dart';

final GoogleMapsFlutterPlatform mapsImplementation = GoogleMapsFlutterPlatform.instance;
if (mapsImplementation is GoogleMapsFlutterAndroid) {
  mapsImplementation.useAndroidViewSurface = false;
}
```

> 
mapsImplementation.useAndroidViewSurface = false;
or
mapsImplementation.useAndroidViewSurface = true;

@giorgio79 
You have to add the below package:
flutter pub add google_maps_flutter_android

And import below
import 'package:google_maps_flutter_android/google_maps_flutter_android.dart';
import 'package:google_maps_flutter_platform_interface/google_maps_flutter_platform_interface.dart';

> The plugin now supports renderer selection, so project-level changes are no longer needed to request the new renderer; see https://pub.dev/packages/google_maps_flutter_android#map-renderer for details. (You will need to add a direct dependency on the `google_maps_flutter_android` implementation package to use that new API).

do we just need to use this
```
final GoogleMapsFlutterPlatform mapsImplementation = GoogleMapsFlutterPlatform.instance;
if (mapsImplementation is GoogleMapsFlutterAndroid) {
  mapsImplementation.useAndroidViewSurface = false;
}
```

or we also need to use 

```
AndroidMapRenderer mapRenderer = AndroidMapRenderer.platformDefault;
// ···
  final GoogleMapsFlutterPlatform mapsImplementation =
      GoogleMapsFlutterPlatform.instance;
  if (mapsImplementation is GoogleMapsFlutterAndroid) {
    WidgetsFlutterBinding.ensureInitialized();
    mapRenderer = await mapsImplementation
        .initializeWithRenderer(AndroidMapRenderer.latest);
  }
```

Facing the same issue. Finally I have resolved it by using **google_maps_flutter 2.1.8**, **google_maps_flutter_android 2.4.3**, **flutter 3.3.10** and the below code in main():

  ```
final GoogleMapsFlutterPlatform mapsImplementation = GoogleMapsFlutterPlatform.instance;
  if (mapsImplementation is GoogleMapsFlutterAndroid) {
    mapsImplementation.useAndroidViewSurface = false;
    mapsImplementation.initializeWithRenderer(AndroidMapRenderer.latest);
  }
```

> Facing the same issue. Finally I have resolved it by using **google_maps_flutter 2.1.8**, **google_maps_flutter_android 2.4.3**, **flutter 3.3.10** and the below code in main():
> 
> ```
> final GoogleMapsFlutterPlatform mapsImplementation = GoogleMapsFlutterPlatform.instance;
> if (mapsImplementation is GoogleMapsFlutterAndroid) {
>   mapsImplementation.useAndroidViewSurface = false;
>   mapsImplementation.initializeWithRenderer(AndroidMapRenderer.latest);
> }
> ```

Using this fixes the crash issue but for some reason, I'm getting an issue where Zoom Controls & Map Toolbar becomes unclickable when calling `mapsImplementation.useAndroidViewSurface = false;`

